{
  "local_port": 53070,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best online coding schools available?",
  "response": "The best online coding schools provide comprehensive curricula, experienced instructors, and flexible learning options to suit different needs. Here are some of the top online coding schools as of 2023:\n\n---\n\n### **1. General Assembly**\n   - **Focus**: Web development, data science, UX design, and more.\n   - **Format**: Part-time, full-time, and self-paced courses.\n   - **Highlights**: Strong career services, industry partnerships, and hands-on projects.\n   - **Website**: [generalassemb.ly](https://generalassemb.ly)\n\n---\n\n### **2. Codecademy**\n   - **Focus**: Web development, data science, computer science, and programming languages.\n   - **Format**: Self-paced, interactive lessons.\n   - **Highlights**: Beginner-friendly, affordable, and a vast library of coding exercises.\n   - **Website**: [codecademy.com](https://www.codecademy.com)\n\n---\n\n### **3. freeCodeCamp**\n   - **Focus**: Web development, data visualization, APIs, and more.\n   - **Format**: Self-paced, free.\n   - **Highlights**: Community-driven, project-based learning, and certifications.\n   - **Website**: [freecodecamp.org](https://www.freecodecamp.org)\n\n---\n\n### **4. Flatiron School**\n   - **Focus**: Software engineering, data science, cybersecurity, and UX/UI design.\n   - **Format**: Full-time, part-time, and self-paced.\n   - **Highlights**: Rigorous curriculum, career coaching, and job placement guarantees.\n   - **Website**: [flatironschool.com](https://flatironschool.com)\n\n---\n\n### **5. Coursera**\n   - **Focus**: Programming, data science, AI, and computer science.\n   - **Format**: Self-paced and instructor-led courses.\n   - **Highlights**: Offers courses from top universities (e.g., Stanford, MIT) and certifications.\n   - **Website**: [coursera.org](https://www.coursera.org)\n\n---\n\n### **6. edX**\n   - **Focus**: Computer science, programming, and data analysis.\n   - **Format**: Self-paced and instructor-led courses.\n   - **Highlights**: Courses from top universities (e.g., Harvard, MIT) and affordable certificates.\n   - **Website**: [edx.org](https://www.edx.org)\n\n---\n\n### **7. Udemy**\n   - **Focus**: Web development, programming, data science, and more.\n   - **Format**: Self-paced video courses.\n   - **Highlights**: Affordable, lifetime access to courses, and a vast library of topics.\n   - **Website**: [udemy.com](https://www.udemy.com)\n\n---\n\n### **8. LeetCode**\n   - **Focus**: Coding interview preparation.\n   - **Format**: Self-paced practice problems.\n   - **Highlights**: Extensive problem sets, mock interviews, and contests.\n   - **Website**: [leetcode.com](https://leetcode.com)\n\n---\n\n### **9. Pluralsight**\n   - **Focus**: Software development, IT, and data science.\n   - **Format**: Self-paced video courses.\n   - **Highlights**: Expert-led courses, skill assessments, and certifications.\n   - **Website**: [pluralsight.com](https://www.pluralsight.com)\n\n---\n\n### **10. The Odin Project**\n   - **Focus**: Full-stack web development.\n   - **Format**: Self-paced, free.\n   - **Highlights**: Project-based learning and a strong community.\n   - **Website**: [theodinproject.com](https://www.theodinproject.com)\n\n---\n\n### **11. Springboard**\n   - **Focus**: Data science, software engineering, cybersecurity, and UX design.\n   - **Format**: Self-paced, mentor-guided.\n   - **Highlights**: Job guarantee, portfolio projects, and career support.\n   - **Website**: [springboard.com](https://www.springboard.com)\n\n---\n\n### **12. Khan Academy**\n   - **Focus**: Computer programming and computer science basics.\n   - **Format**: Self-paced, free.\n   - **Highlights**: Beginner-friendly and accessible.\n   - **Website**: [khanacademy.org](https://www.khanacademy.org)\n\n---\n\n### **13. Lambda School (now BloomTech)**\n   - **Focus**: Full-stack web development and data science.\n   - **Format**: Full-time and part-time.\n   - **Highlights**: Income Share Agreement (ISA) model and career support.\n   - **Website**: [bloomtech.com](https://www.bloomtech.com)\n\n---\n\n### **14. Skillcrush**\n   - **Focus**: Web development, design, and digital marketing.\n   - **Format**: Self-paced, affordable.\n   - **Highlights**: Beginner-friendly, flexible, and career-focused.\n   - **Website**: [skillcrush.com](https://skillcrush.com)\n\n---\n\n### **15. W3Schools**\n   - **Focus**: Web development and programming languages.\n   - **Format**: Self-paced, free and paid options.\n   - **Highlights**: Beginner-friendly, quick reference guides, and interactive exercises.\n   - **Website**: [w3schools.com](https://www.w3schools.com)\n\n---\n\nWhen choosing the best online coding school, consider factors like your learning style, budget, career goals, and the specific skills you want to acquire. Many platforms offer free trials or introductory courses to help you decide.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
